If `__attribute__((packed))` is not specified, the calculation of sizeof would be optimized for performance by compiler, here is an example:
```
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdint.h>

struct not_packed {
    uint8_t one_byte;
    uint16_t two_bytes;
};

struct packed {
    uint8_t one_byte;
    uint16_t two_bytes;
} __attribute__((packed));

int main()
{
    // Some compiler would be 4
    printf("not_packed size: %lu \n", sizeof(struct not_packed));
    // Always be 3
    printf("packed size: %lu", sizeof(struct packed));

    return 0;
}
```

It can be simply reproduced on some online compiler website such as [onelinegdb.com](https://www.onlinegdb.com/online_c_compiler). If there is a mechanism to avoid this problem in `libpldm`, please let me know, thanks.

